"v. 抗议；规劝 【英】 v. 抗议，规劝(to earnestly present and urge reasons in opposition; expostulate) 【考】 remonstrance : offend(dissuade)/ reprehensible : censure /syllogism :disprove(抗议为了劝止/斥责 为了责难/推论为了反 驳)remonstrator : dissuade / applicant : appeal(抗议者提出反对/申 请者提出诉请) 【记】 re(重新)+monstr(显 现)+ate→显出对别人 的不满→抗议； 【同】 参考：monster(怪物)派生词：remonstranc e （n. 抗议，抱怨） 【例】 to remonstrate against his behavior v. 抗议 = expostulate 【记】源于: monster(n 怪物; 妖怪), 人们抗议出现的东西. 【参】remonstrance(n 抗议) 【类】remonstrance: offend[dissuade] = syllogism: disprove抗议为了劝止 = 三段论为了反驳remonstrator: dissuade = applicant: appeal抗议者提出反对 = 申请者提出请求 【记】demonstrate 示范，示威 remonstrate (v.)  1590s, ""make plain,"" back-formation from remonstration, or else from Medieval Latin remonstratus, past participle of  remonstrare ""to demonstrate"" (see remonstrance). Meaning ""to exhibit or present strong reasons against"" is from 1690s. Related: Remonstrated; remonstrating."
